


Monsieur
LaHaie 3e. Avril 1783



Nous savons ici, par Lettres de Hambourg du 25 du pass, que Mr. Votre fils, aprs Sy tre arrt quelques jours, en toit reparti le 23.1
Voici des Lettres Amricaines venues par la poste dAngleterre. Celle de Mr. Guild Sest trouve dans un paquet entierement us & [382] [383][384]ouvert dun ct. Il contenoit deux brochures: Letter to the Abb Raynal by Ths. Payne, & Catalogus eorum qui in Universitate Harvardiana Cantabrigi in Rep. Massachsi. ab ao 1642 ad an. 1782 alicujus gradus laurea donati sunt.2 Jai cru devoir dposer ces deux pieces dans votre Secretaire, & vous envoyer Seulement la Lettre.3
A certain face you would not meet in a wood, you will meet it, with his influenza in the future Congress of final pacification, at which I am assured he is appointed to assist. I Sat next him yesterday at the F. Ambassadors, who gave a Diplomatic Dinner.4 We were much talkative together about the several climates of Russia nearly corresponding with those of our States, and the extensiveness of both, about Kamtschatka, Capt. Cook, the Caspian Sea and Mount Caucase, which he told me he went through. There, said I, you may possibly have traaden on some of the Steps of Alexander the great. He Smiled, and I too, fancying him horded, when there, with the modern Hircanians, so formidable to Caravans.5
Je Suis avec grand respect, De Votre Exce. / le trs-humble & trs / obissant serviteur
Dumas

